<CHARACTERISTICS_OF_STUDIES MODIFIED="2014-06-09 15:38:13 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<CHARACTERISTICS_OF_INCLUDED_STUDIES MODIFIED="2014-06-09 15:38:13 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]" SORT_BY="STUDY" USER_DEF_1_ENABLED="NO" USER_DEF_2_ENABLED="NO" USER_DEF_3_ENABLED="NO">
<INCLUDED_CHAR MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:29:10 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]" STUDY_ID="STD-Feltner-2003">
<CHAR_METHODS MODIFIED="2014-05-27 09:57:52 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>
<B>Study design: </B>Randomized controlled trial</P>
</CHAR_METHODS>
<CHAR_PARTICIPANTS MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:29:10 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>
<B>Diagnosis</B>:DSM-IV Generalized Anxiety DIsorder</P>
<P>
<B>Method of Diagnosis</B>: Mini Neuropsychiatric Interview (MINI) "Subjects were outpatients aged 18 years or older, recruited either from clinic referrals or advertisements, provided they ment DSM-IV criteria...".</P>
<P>
<B>Age</B>: Placebo: mean age 37.8, (SD 10.8, range 18 -- 67; Pregabalin 50 mg TID Mean 37.9 (10.9) range 19 -- 73; Pregabalin 200 mg TID mean 36.3 (10.9) range 20 -- 74; lorazepam 2 mg TID mean 39.2 (11.7) range 21 --73)</P>
<P>
<B>Location</B>: USA</P>
<P>
<B>Co-morbidities</B>: Some co-morbid neuroses allowed.</P>
<P>"Patients were excluded if they suffered from another axis I disorder except dysthymia, simple phobia, social phobia, somatization disorder, or a history of major depressive disorder (current major depressive disorder was excluded). In addition, patients with severe personality disorders (antisocial or borderline); drug or alcohol abuse/dependence (active within the last six months); and suicide risk as judged by the clinician (on the basis of history and examination) or according to current severity of suicidal ideation (a HAM-D item 3 score &gt;= 2) were excluded. In patients with comorbid psychiatric diagnoses, GAD was required to be the primary disorder...."</P>
<P>
<B>Adjunctive Therapy</B>: Not stated.</P>
<P>
<B>Adjunctive Medication</B>: Not stated</P>
</CHAR_PARTICIPANTS>
<CHAR_INTERVENTIONS MODIFIED="2014-05-27 10:17:45 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>Participants were randomly assigned to either:</P>
<P>(1) <U>Experimental Arm</U>
</P>
<P>
<B>Duration</B>: Four weeks</P>
<P>
<B>Treatment Protocol</B>: Pregabalin 50 mg TID or Pregabalin 200 mg TID</P>
<P>
<B>Therapist/Face-to-Face Contact</B>: weekly assessments</P>
<P>(2) <U>Comparator arm</U>
</P>
<P>
<B>Duration</B>: Four weeks</P>
<P>
<B>Treatment Protocol</B>: Lorazepam 2 mg TID</P>
<P>
<B>Therapist/Face-to-Face Contact</B>: weekly assessments.</P>
</CHAR_INTERVENTIONS>
<CHAR_OUTCOMES MODIFIED="2014-05-27 10:21:46 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>
<B>Timepoints for Assessment</B>: On week prior to treatment, weekly for four weeks of treatment (including day zero) and one week post (during which drugs tapered to zero).</P>
<P>
<B>Primary outcome</B>:</P>
<P>(1) GAD symptoms: Hamilton Anxiety Scale (HAM-A) at day 28 (end of treatment).</P>
<P>
<B>Secondary outcome</B>:</P>
<P>(1) Serial (weekly) clinical measurement: HAM-A R</P>
<P>(2) Clinician Impression: CGI</P>
<P>(3) Hamiton Depression Scale (HAM-D) at screening and termination. </P>
<P>(4) Adverse effects: using the COSTART checklist.</P>
<P>(5) Physician withdrawal checklist (PWC)</P>
</CHAR_OUTCOMES>
<CHAR_NOTES MODIFIED="2014-05-27 10:25:43 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>ITT population of 271 reported in paper. </P>
<P>Paper written in Pfizer Global Research and Development Laboratories (Michigan) in conjunction with Eastside Comprehensive Mdical Services (New York) and Clinical Studies Ltd, Philadelphia. Sponsored by Park-Davis Pharmaceutical Research. <BR/>
</P>
</CHAR_NOTES>
</INCLUDED_CHAR>
<INCLUDED_CHAR MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:57:34 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]" STUDY_ID="STD-Pande-2003">
<CHAR_METHODS MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:09:35 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>
<B>Study design: </B>Randomized controlled trial</P>
</CHAR_METHODS>
<CHAR_PARTICIPANTS MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:57:34 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>
<B>Diagnosis</B>:DSM-IV Generalized Anxiety DIsorder</P>
<P>
<B>Method of Diagnosis</B>: Mini Nueropsychiatric Interview (MINI) "Subjects were outpatients aged 18 years or older, recruited either from clinic referrals or advertisements, provided they ment DSM-IV criteria...". Covi Anxiety score &gt;=9 Raskin Depression score &lt;=7.</P>
<P>
<B>Age</B>: All patients mean age 35.8 (SD 11.1);Placebo: 35.7, (11.5); Pregabalin 50 mg TID Mean 37.9 (11.8); Pregabalin 200 mg TID mean 35.5 (11.2) ; lorazepam 2 mg TID mean 33.9 (9.7);</P>
<P>
<B>Location</B>: USA</P>
<P>
<B>Co-morbidities</B>:</P>
<P>Some co-morbid neuroses allowed.</P>
<P>"Patients were excluded if they suffered from another axis I disorder except dysthymia, simple phobia, social phobia, somatization disorder, or a history of major depressive disorder ..."</P>
<P>Must be medication free for two weeks before enrollment</P>
<P>
<B>Adjunctive Therapy</B>: No more than two nights a week.</P>
<P>
<B>Adjunctive Medication</B>: Zolpidem 5mg at night for sleep.</P>
</CHAR_PARTICIPANTS>
<CHAR_INTERVENTIONS MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:09:35 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>Participants were randomly assigned to either:</P>
<P>(1) <U>Experimental Arm</U>
</P>
<P>
<B>Duration</B>: Four weeks</P>
<P>
<B>Treatment Protocol</B>: Pregabalin 50 mg TID or Pregabalin 200 mg TID</P>
<P>
<B>Therapist/Face-to-Face Contact</B>: weekly assessments</P>
<P>(2) <U>Comparator arm</U>
</P>
<P>
<B>Duration</B>: Four weeks</P>
<P>
<B>Treatment Protocol</B>: Lorazepam 2 mg TID</P>
<P>
<B>Therapist/Face-to-Face Contact</B>: weekly assessments.</P>
</CHAR_INTERVENTIONS>
<CHAR_OUTCOMES MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:28:57 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>
<B>Timepoints for Assessment</B>: On week prior to treatment, weekly for four weeks of treatment (including day zero) and one week post (during which drugs tapered to zero).</P>
<P>
<B>Primary outcome</B>:</P>
<P>(1) GAD symptoms: Hamilton Anxiety Scale (HAM-A) at day 28 (end of treatment).</P>
<P>
<B>Secondary outcome</B>:</P>
<P>(1) Serial (weekly) clinical measurement: HAM-A</P>
<P>(2) Clinician Global Impression: CGI</P>
<P>(3) Physician withdrawal checklist (PWC)</P>
</CHAR_OUTCOMES>
<CHAR_NOTES MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:32:42 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>ITT population of 276 reported in paper.</P>
<P>Paper written in Pfizer Global Research and Development Laboratories (Michigan) in conjunction with Pacific Northwest Clinical Research (Oregon) Duke University (North Carolina), Seattle Clinical Research Centre (Washington), Institute for Health Sciences (Michigan) and the Pacific Clinical Research Medical Group (California). Sponsored by Park-Davis Pharmaceutical Research.<BR/>
</P>
</CHAR_NOTES>
</INCLUDED_CHAR>
<INCLUDED_CHAR MODIFIED="2014-06-09 15:38:13 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]" STUDY_ID="STD-Rickels-2005">
<CHAR_METHODS MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:33:24 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>
<B>Study design: </B>Randomized controlled trial</P>
</CHAR_METHODS>
<CHAR_PARTICIPANTS MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:58:19 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>
<B>Diagnosis</B>:DSM-IV Generalized Anxiety DIsorder</P>
<P>
<B>Method of Diagnosis</B>: Patients recruited from outpatients clinics and advertisements in local medial. Aged 18 years or older, with a Mini Neuropsychiatric Interview (MINI) diagnosis of GAD; HAM-A score &gt;= 20 and Covi Anxiety Scale &gt;= 9. </P>
<P>
<B>Age</B>: Placebo mean age 41 (SD 12);Pregabalin 300 mg./d Mean 38 (10); Pregabalin 450 mg/d mean 38 (12); alprazolam 1.5 mg./d mean 40 (12);</P>
<P>
<B>Location</B>: USA</P>
<P>
<B>Co-morbidities</B>: Minimal.: Excluded if depressive symptoms (Raskin Depression Scale &gt;= 7, or current or past history of bipolar, current but not past depressive disorder, schizophrenia or schizoaffective disorder, social anxiety disorder, panic disorder, agoraphobia, obsessive-compulsive disorder, acute stress disorder, post traumatic stress disorder, an eating disorder, or a positive drug screen (including benzodiazepines). </P>
<P>
<B>Adjunctive Therapy</B>: No.</P>
<P>
<B>Adjunctive Medication</B>: Nil.</P>
</CHAR_PARTICIPANTS>
<CHAR_INTERVENTIONS MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:53:51 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>Participants were randomly assigned to either:</P>
<P>(1) <U>Experimental Arm</U>
</P>
<P>
<B>Duration</B>: Four weeks</P>
<P>
<B>Treatment Protocol</B>: Pregabalin 300 mg./d, 450 mg./d, and 600 mg./d in three divided doses. Doses commenced at 300 mg./d for all and then titrated up for the higher doses using a fixed schedule. </P>
<P>
<B>Therapist/Face-to-Face Contact</B>: weekly assessments</P>
<P>(2) <U>Comparator arm</U>
</P>
<P>
<B>Duration</B>: Four weeks</P>
<P>
<B>Treatment Protocol</B>: alprazolam 1.5 mg./d. Dose stated at 0.5 mg/d and was titrated up according to a fixed schedule</P>
<P>
<B>Therapist/Face-to-Face Contact</B>: weekly assessments.</P>
</CHAR_INTERVENTIONS>
<CHAR_OUTCOMES MODIFIED="2014-05-30 15:54:51 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>
<B>Timepoints for Assessment</B>: On week prior to treatment, weekly for four weeks of treatment (including day zero) and one week post (during which drugs tapered to zero).</P>
<P>
<B>Primary outcome</B>:</P>
<P>(1) GAD symptoms: Hamilton Anxiety Scale (HAM-A) at day 28 (end of treatment).</P>
<P>
<B>Secondary outcome</B>:</P>
<P>(1) Serial (weekly) clinical measurement: HAM-A</P>
<P>(2) Clinician Global Impression: CGI</P>
<P>(3) Endicott Work Productivity Scale</P>
</CHAR_OUTCOMES>
<CHAR_NOTES MODIFIED="2014-06-09 15:38:13 +1200" MODIFIED_BY="[Empty name]">
<P>ITT population of 454 reported in paper.</P>
<P>Paper written in Pfizer Global Research and Development Laboratories (Michigan) in conjunction with Department of Psychiatry, University of Pennsylvania, Southeast Halth Consultants (South Carolina, Institute for Health Sciences (Michigan) and the Pacific Clinical Research Medical Group (California). Sponsored by Pfizer Inc.<BR/>
</P>
</CHAR_NOTES>
</INCLUDED_CHAR>
